https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/qGXbCd8mw2K6yNcW3Cegcm8YSXx.jpg A fascinating account of the presidency of Andrew Jackson, who was both one of America's great presidents and a borderline tyrant. The seventh president shook up the glossy world of Washington, DC with his "common-man" methods and ideals, but also oversaw one of the most controversial events in American history: the forced removal of Indian tribes, including the Cherokees, from their homes. Andrew Jackson: Good, Evil & The Presidency
